## Plan Summary

**Only one file needs to change: `src/routes.ts`**

The tests already exist and define the exact expected behavior — I just need to update the `GET /users` handler. Here's the approach:

### What changes
Replace the current `res.json(users)` with pagination logic:

```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10;

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const offset     = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(offset, offset + limit);

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

### Why this satisfies all requirements
| Requirement | How it's handled |
|---|---|
| `page` default 1, `limit` default 10 | `parseInt(...) \|\| 1` / `\|\| 10` fallback |
| Correct response shape | Wraps result in `{ data, pagination }` |
| Out-of-range page → empty array | `Array.slice()` returns `[]` naturally when offset ≥ total |
| Existing tests still pass | `GET /users/:id` handler is untouched |

No other files need to be modified — `src/types.ts`, `src/data.ts`, `src/app.ts`, and the test file all stay as-is.
